<def f='linux-5.3.1/include/rdma/ib_verbs.h' l='3138' ll='3142' type='bool rdma_cap_af_ib(const struct ib_device * device, u8 port_num)'/>
<doc f='linux-5.3.1/include/rdma/ib_verbs.h' l='3125'>/**
 * rdma_cap_af_ib - Check if the port of device has the capability
 * Native Infiniband Address.
 * @device: Device to check
 * @port_num: Port number to check
 *
 * InfiniBand addressing uses a port&apos;s GUID + Subnet Prefix to make a default
 * GID.  RoCE uses a different mechanism, but still generates a GID via
 * a prescribed mechanism and port specific data.
 *
 * Return: true if the port uses a GID address to identify devices on the
 * network.
 */</doc>
